reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is the best car seat I have ever owned. It is well made, very comfortable, fits my car seat perfectly and has just enough height.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It fit perfectly!
reviews.reviewText: It works fabulously in Acura MDX. It lifted my seat up so I have full vision over my steering wheel and it’s very comfortable. I love it and I will purchase another for out second car.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice seat cushion
reviews.reviewText: Great for long distance driving, extending seat life, added height for shorter drivers. I would recommend adding a strap that would fasten behind your seat to keep it in place when entering or exiting your vehicle. It's annoying to keep moving back into place. It's comfortable, doesnt hold smells, adequate thickness and helps with butt pain on long distance driving.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Its great for the car and my computer chair. It helps with my lower back issues.
reviews.reviewText: This seat is nice and large. It fits great with my computer chair. It's also nice and cool and I wont get hot. I am ordering one for my car. I have problems with my lower back and had knee surgery. I purchased another pillow and it was too small and made out of a material that feels like you can make bed covers with it. Its grate for another chair that I have downstairs that is smaller. Highly recommend the seat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Significantly increased comfort
reviews.reviewText: I bought a Camry hybrid last year and it makes no sense to me why Toyota would make a car with such great mileage and poor comfort. I decided to give this cushion a try because if I can’t take a road trip then what was the point? Previously driving past 3 hours was pretty uncomfortable. I drove to New Orleans in two 5.5 hour shifts on consecutive days because I still don’t want to be in the car too much. Well it’s gotta be 2 to 3 times more comfortable with fatigue also reduced following. I actually dont really like to use on short trips when I’m at home because it will move a little as it has no strap. Maybe dycem on bottom would help that. Regardless I will order another for my daughter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very well made and comfy. Fits perfectly but it smells awful. Yes, I aired it out but it still smells like acetone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfort is available with the addition to our car!
reviews.reviewText: On long trips, whether I was driving or in the passenger seat, I would get extreme pain in my right leg due to degenerative disc disease. The seat, added on top of the sports style seats in our car, really has eliminated the pain. It stays in place, no moving around. And it has made it easier to get in and out of a low car.
